Basic knowledge is aquired using guided independent work (videolectures, written text) and confirmed by auditory seminars with help of supervisors. Aquired knowledge and skills are practiced via assessing of geriatric patients during seminars and independent practical work. At the end of the course each student presents summary of assessment and plan for further management of a geriatric patient according to defined instructions.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Students learn to recognize and apply peculiarities of geriatric medicine necessary for general physicians: common health and coping problems in older and frail patients, use of comprehensive geriatric assessment, specific features of treatment, care and prevention of geriatric patients.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Students who have passed the programme successfully: 1.	know general peculiarities of manifestation of illnesses and treatment in older people (clinical examination, assessment before scheduled surgery, application of clinical guidelines in frail older people, potentially inappropriate medicines for older people); 2.	are able to perform basic comprehensive geriatric assessment (interRAI CA as an example) and use data of complete geriatric comprehensive assessment for planning of following diagnostics, treatment and care; 3.	know manifestations of essential geriatric syndromes/ problems and are capable of considering them in clinical practise (frailty in old age, dementia, delirium, malnutrition, falls, pain, urinary incontinence); 4.	are aware of general principles of long term health and social care arrangement and roles of different specialists; understand the role of a physician in an interdisciplinary care team; 5.	know and utilise principles of geriatric ethics (ageism, elderly abuse, advance directives).
